Thanks for the report @WardLT! Just to clarify, do you need to set the default dynamically, or would something like this work:

```
@App('python', dfk)
def f(d=None):
    if data is None:
        data = pd.DataFrame({'x': [None,2,[3]]})
    return d.sum()
f().result()
```
There is a nice discussion [here](http://docs.python-guide.org/en/latest/writing/gotchas/) on why you might want to avoid mutable default arguments to a function. Let me know what your requirements are and will go from there.

FWIW what you could do instead (and what might be easier with many modules) is this:

```python
import importlib

for module in ['matplotlib', ...]:
    try:
        importlib.import_module(module)
    except ImportError:
        raise ImportError("{} is required".format(module))
```

