@NikolajBjorner Crude indeed :)

I'd be very happy to see this PR merged but I think it's worth thinking about what we want to do for OSX. I designed the ``MakeRuleCmd`` carefully to make it very difficult to accidently install stuff outside the install prefix because doing so is likely a mistake. This is why you are having to remove those asserts.

I don't think your patch works though because you'll still end up with ``$(DESTDIR)$(PREFIX)`` in front of any absolute path you try to force into the ``install_files()``, ``remove_installed_files()``, etc... methods. The install won't end up where you want.

